DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "answerHints.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("LimitedNumeric");

$a=random(2,10,1);
$b=random(2,10,1);

$ans1=Compute($a-$b);
$ans2=Compute($a*(-$b));

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Evaluate these expressions:

a.   [`` [$a]-[$b] =  ``]  [________]{$ans1}
a.   [`` [$a](-[$b]) =  ``]  [________]{$ans2}


END_PGML

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

a. This problem is a straightforward subtraction:  
[``
  \begin{aligned}[t]
  [$a]-[$b]  & =  [$ans1] 
  \end{aligned}
  ``]
a. Notice the difference from Part a. Since there is no operation symbol between [`[$a]`] and [`(-[$b])`], it implies multiplication.  
[``
  \begin{aligned}[t]
  [$a](-[$b])& = [$a] \cdot (-[$b]) \\
  & = [$ans2] 
  \end{aligned}
  ``]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();


